# Agent Handoff Contract

All agents in the OpenBook Author studio accept and produce this schema.

## Router Handoff (input to execution agents)

```yaml
issue: <number>
title: <string>
classification: bug | feature | docs | refactor | test | design | unknown
confidence: <0.00–1.00>
agent: debug-agent | feature-agent | docs-agent | refactor-agent | test-agent | ui-agent
priority: low | medium | high | critical
estimated_scope: small | medium | large | epic
escalate: true | false
recommendation: <string | null>  # required when escalate is true
relevant_adrs: []  # full slugs, e.g. ADR-0001-guidebook-block-model — from @architecture-memory
deliverables:
  - <item>
success_criteria:
  - <criterion>
context:
  labels: []
  linked_files: []
  summary: <1–3 sentences>
workflow:
  - <current-agent>
  - review-agent
  - pr-creator-agent
```

## Execution Handoff (output from execution agents → review-agent)

```yaml
issue: <number>
source_agent: <agent-id>
status: complete | blocked | needs_human
changes_summary: <what was done>
files_touched: []
deliverables_completed: []
success_criteria_met: []
adrs_consulted: []  # full ADR slugs read and followed
architecture_change: true | false
adr_proposal: null  # or { id: ADR-0005-short-slug, title: "...", action: new|supersede, supersedes: ADR-XXXX-short-slug }
open_questions: []
next_agent: review-agent
```

## Review Handoff (output from review-agent → pr-creator-agent)

```yaml
issue: <number>
source_agent: review-agent
verdict: approved | changes_requested | blocked
findings: []
security_flags: []
a11y_flags: []
adr_compliance: pass | adr_missing | adr_conflict
next_agent: pr-creator-agent
```

### ADR compliance gate

When `architecture_change: true` in the execution handoff:

- `pass` — `adrs_consulted` shows Accepted ADRs were followed, or `adr_proposal` is present for merge
- `adr_missing` — architectural change with no ADR coverage
- `adr_conflict` — implementation contradicts an Accepted ADR without supersede proposal
